The breakfast buffet is actually pretty good with a large selection of offerings. George Michael background music and real eggs. It doesn't get much better than this... actually it does... the kiddos eat for free 👍
Really good food at a good price. Kids eat free with adult purchase. Staff were friendly and kind. This Holiday Inn is a wonderful place to stay.

The plates were very messy and had the sauces splattered all over the place. I think they didn't change the place mats between customers, which I find quite disgusting. The food was unevenly cooked, my burger was well done in some places and very rare in others.

Food very good. Had the buffet dinner. Pizza crust must have been made from scratch on the premises. Also enjoyed the chicken dish. Service was good at breakfast buffet, server taking my omelet order right away. All enjoyable.
Excellent food and great customer service. Highly recommended

Good little buffet for lunch.
Stopped in for breakfast. Great food but a little overpriced for breakfast.
Good breakfast! Sweet employees Food was fresh and was a good variety
Neat , convenient and clean. Decent selection, delicious.

I repeated a meal I had a couple years back. French Onion soup and Crab Cakes. Good but not as good as last time. Broth was beefy but salty. Crab Cakes were a bit mealy with filler. I asked for extra Old Bay on the side to account for the lack of it in the cakes. That helped as I like my Old Bay after 30 years in Baltimore. Service was upscale and so was the price. I'll try it again next time perhaps.
I've gotten food poisoning from this place...I've  Been sick for over 5 days straight... be awear of everything...
very good food specially service.
Dinner buffet was ok, nothing to write home about. Service was good though.
Food sub par and overpriced.  Everyone in my group got the buffet and it was seriously lacking .  Cold chicken, soggy microwave pizza and the list goes on.  Skip this place.

Legitimately the worst appetizer and steak I've ever had in my life. My $26 steak was the equivalent of the steak used in a McDonald's steak breakfast sandwich -- that's barely an exaggeration. Absolutely terrible and wouldn't recommend this place to anyone. I never leave poor reviews or reviews in general; this place absolutely deserves it. Go somewhere else. It's basically robbery with some terrible food given to you  in exchange.

I have breakfast over here. It was very nice. I choice breakfast buffet. Breakfast buffet time 06:30-10:30. The food was delicious 😋! It’s very nice convenient restaurant! A lot of people come here ate breakfast!!! Good service!!! Flavorful salads. Home - made soups. Traditional bistro entree’s with imaginative twists. Desserts 🍨 and wines to savor.👍👍👍👍👍
Mediocre food but great service.

Go here if you want to pay $24 for a buffet where they try to pass off roast beef as New York strip and charge you $18 for a Caesar salad. Also will tell you at the door that kids eat free and then when you pay they'll tell you that you actually need a coupon.  Very dishonest and shady little place. Food wasn't actually half bad, but I just can't shake the feeling of being robbed
Overpriced
Wonderful environment to eat

It’s inside of the hotel. Felt like I was waking into one of those cruise line dining halls.  Food was good kinda pricey. Service was ok. We walked in after the breakfast buffet so they were cleaning up after that.

Way better than I anticipated. It was so hot today, and we were happy to have no wait. Margarita was strong (bonus). I had the Food Truck Rollover (chicken wrap) and it was really good. My boys shared the Nachos, delicious. Husband had the salmon salad. It was our waitress's first day, she was really nice.
Average food, server Jose was great
Good service
Excellent food very good on buffets. Seafood newberg A+ Will gladly comeback Highly recomend for any occasion
One of the worst dining experiences I've had in a while.

Mandatory 18% tip for large parties that they don’t mention on their menu OR when they tell you the price. We had to scavenge for utensils because half of us were missing forks. Food was nasty. Bland, and when it did have flavor, it wasn’t good. For a $25 dollar buffet, plus the tip we never were alerted of, it was a $30 buffet. The most expensive and by far the nastiest buffet I’ve ever been to. The service didn’t justify the fee. Had to constantly ask for refills, waiter had an attitude and was inattentive and she rushed us out of the restaurant before the closing time. The entire party wishes we just went to McDonald’s...and we don’t eat McDonald’s.

Terrible! The bartender overfilled the glass with ice to account with the poor drink quality and pour. The nachos were sub par for the money and had virtually no meat. Even the hotel staff was rude. One lady even slammed into me while I was walking to the bathroom and she didn't even say a word to acknowledge or apologize.
For the first time in my life I sent a meal back. The chicken in my chicken sandwich could have been used to patch a shoe. Pathetic
(Translated by Google) Note 10 service, with food for all tastes, very well prepared and tasty.  (Original) Atendimento nota 10, com alimentos para todos os gostos, muito bem elaborados e saborosos.
Overpriced for mediocre food. Service was good but that was all. Breakfast buffet wasn't worth it. Went to McDonald's the next morning.
Didn't get what I ordered, cold eggs and over priced
Just had dinner very good choices. Salad was very fresh and staff was kind and curtious.
Definitely not worth it. Service left something to be desired. Food was still good though. Would still just walk down the street to go somewhere that doesn't charge four times what they should.
Had the dinner buffet. Not a huge selection but very good food.  Salmon was excellent! Our waiter, Ashebir, was great with our two children.

We fined both Wednesday and Thursday evenings and both nights we had the pleasure of being g served by Ashebir. Such a great man, very attentive, pleasant and offered great advice during our stay. Too bad this fine man isn't in Illinois. Hope you know what a great worker you have in this man.

Excellent food excellent service if you get a chance ask for Asheber as your waiter. He is the best waiter I have ever had and I have been to some high class restaurants this man is the best waiter you can find, great service, great food, and drinks.
Buffet was great waiter got us Ann omelette which was outstanding. Mario was betty attentive and a super waiter.

We ate breakfast at the Capitol Bistro every morning during our stay at the Holiday Inn (4 mornings). They have a good selection of items if you decide to do the buffett and the food was very good. We had the best server, Desta, she  was extremely attentive from knowing our drink order on the 3rd day to giving us to-go cups for coffee. She also made a point to make my daughter feel special on her birthday by bringing a piece of cake with a candle and singing Happy birthday. Something she definitely did not expect during breakfast! Desta is attentive, kind, hardworking and indespensible member of the Holiday Inn team.
No gravy with biscuitsome even after we asked. My husbands chair was full of syrup when it was finally cleaned his food was cold. Last night the food was terrible.
We tried it only for breakfast. Large buffet. Good option.

The food is mediocre, though the chicken salad was good. The service is awful though, inattentive and at times adversarial. Best case scenario is they take ages to get you a single drink. Capitol Bistro lives up to the stereotypes you hear about Hotel restaurants and bad service.
Food was ok, but nothing special for the exorbitant prices.  Christmas day nothing else close by was open or I'd have gone elsewhere.
Breakfast Buffet was excellent, service was amazing, made to order omelets and otherwise great selection. Was a bit pricey at $17 per person

They told us that they recently changed their menu and to tell them if their should be any changes made. But I don't think that that is necessary. I had the crab cakes and thought that they were delicious. The service was excellent and the waiters were very friendly. There was a party of around 25 that came in a little after us and they seemed to have no problem taking care of them.
Weather was predicted to be bad tonight so I came to the hotel restaurant.   The buffet sounded good but was a total disappointment.  I'm not sure how food can be that awful.  Avoid this place.
Great  service and good food
